Column.commentInRDBMS: Ecommerce

Column.commentInRDBMS: Base for Goodyear, Dunlop & Kelly

Column.commentInRDBMS: Net Acquisition Cost

Column.name: speed_rating
Column.commentInRDBMS: Alphabetic value that matches to the maximum MPH the tire is capable of reaching without damage to the tire.

Column.name: load_range
Column.commentInRDBMS: Alphabetic ply rating of the tire.

Column.name: revs_mile
Column.commentInRDBMS: Tire's revolutions per mile.

Column.name: revs_km
Column.commentInRDBMS: Tire's revolutions per kilometer.

Column.name: min_rim_width
Column.commentInRDBMS: Minimum width of the wheel the tire is designed to be mounted on.

Column.name: max_rim_width
Column.commentInRDBMS: Maximum width of the wheel the tire is designed to be mounted on.

Column.name: single_max_load
Column.commentInRDBMS: Numerical value (in lbs.) of the single load index.

Column.name: single_max_psi
Column.commentInRDBMS: Unused field. Currently using ud_capacity_psi field instead.

Column.name: dual_max_load
Column.commentInRDBMS: Numerical value (in lbs.) of the dual load index.

Column.name: dual_max_psi
Column.commentInRDBMS: Unused field. Currently using ud_capacity_psi field instead.

Column.name: tread_depth
Column.commentInRDBMS: Verticle measurement between the top of the tire's tread rubber and bottom of the tire's deepest groove in 1/32 inch (currently unused).

Column.name: type
Column.commentInRDBMS: Custom field used for Tools Group to identify item type.

Column.name: section_width
Column.commentInRDBMS: 3 digit numerical portion of the tire size that identifies the cross section of a tire in millimeters.

Column.name: aspect_ratio
Column.commentInRDBMS: Percentage ratio of the tire's sidewall height from rim to tread of the section width of the tire.

Column.name: utqg_wear
Column.commentInRDBMS: Numerical value of the UTQG (Uniform Tire Quality Grading) rating.

Column.name: utqg_traction
Column.commentInRDBMS: Alphabetic value of the traction portion of the UTQG (Uniform Tire Quality Grading) rating.

Column.name: utqg_tem
Column.commentInRDBMS: Alphabetic value of the temperature portion of the UTQG (Uniform Tire Quality Grading) rating.

Column.name: sidewall
Column.commentInRDBMS: Condensed description of the visual appearance of the tire sidewall (side portion of the tire).

Column.name: warranty
Column.commentInRDBMS: Manufacturer's Tire Mileage warranty.

Column.name: warranty_km
Column.commentInRDBMS: Manufacturer's Tire Mileage warranty in KM.

Column.name: country
Column.commentInRDBMS: Country of manufacture.

Column.name: run_flat
Column.commentInRDBMS: Flag to identify tires which can operate upto 50miles at 50mph at 0 (zero) psi.

Column.name: oem
Column.commentInRDBMS: Identifies if a tire is Original Equipment Manufacturer (OEM).

Column.name: uhp
Column.commentInRDBMS: Identifies if the tire is Ultra High Performance (UHP; V-speed rated or higher).

Column.name: rim_diameter
Column.commentInRDBMS: Tire diameter measured in inches.

Column.name: winter
Column.commentInRDBMS: Identifies is a tire is rated for Winter use.

Column.name: load_ind
Column.commentInRDBMS: Numerical value used to determine relative load carrying capabilities.

Column.name: utqg
Column.commentInRDBMS: Uniform Tire Quality Grading rating.

Column.name: service_type
Column.commentInRDBMS: Type of vehical/service for which the tire was designed for.

Column.name: full_size
Column.commentInRDBMS: Complete tire size as described by the manufacturer.

Column.name: load_speed
Column.commentInRDBMS: Combination of the complete load index and speed rating.

Column.name: core
Column.commentInRDBMS: Core item of all TLCs.

Column.name: net_special
Column.commentInRDBMS: Flag to identify if tire is on a pricing special from supplier (currently unused).

Column.name: net_special_price
Column.commentInRDBMS: Reduced cost of the tire if tire on net special (currently unused).

Column.name: pending_dd
Column.commentInRDBMS: pending discontinuation flag (currently unused).

Column.name: tier
Column.commentInRDBMS: Numerical value of the tier (currently unused; use class1_id instead).

Column.name: overall_diameter
Column.commentInRDBMS: Outer diameter of the tire measured in the center of the tread.

Column.name: tread
Column.commentInRDBMS: Verticle measurement between the top of the tire's tread rubber and bottom of the tire's deepest groove in 1/32 inch.

Column.name: capacity_psi
Column.commentInRDBMS: Represents maximum capacity of the tire that can be inflated to under cold pressure. Stamped on the sidewall of the tire.

Column.name: dual_load_index
Column.commentInRDBMS: Numerical value used to determine relative load carrying capabilities in dual application.

Column.name: dd
Column.commentInRDBMS: Flag to identify discontinued item (at item level).

Column.name: tread_pattern
Column.commentInRDBMS: Tread pattern (currently unused).

Column.name: studdable
Column.commentInRDBMS: Represents if the tire can accept studs.

Column.name: foam
Column.commentInRDBMS: Goodyear sound detonating technology.

Column.name: application
Column.commentInRDBMS: Identifies whether a tire is consumer, commercial or industrial.

Column.name: sales_tier
Column.commentInRDBMS: Same as class1_id also knowns as brand_group_id (currently unused).

Column.name: extended_desc
Column.commentInRDBMS: Extended/full description of the item’s pattern

Column.name: default_product_group
Column.commentInRDBMS: Indicates if an item is Tire or non-tire

Column.name: msf
Column.commentInRDBMS: mountain snowflake applicable or not

Column.name: season_type
Column.commentInRDBMS: Season type associated with the tire
